                "Mumbai, India."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "SAMPLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "Al target 2 mm thick and 45 mm in diameter, was",
                "mounted inside a small chamber of about 1mm wall",
                "thickness"
              ]
            }
          ],
          "DETECTOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "SCIN"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " BC501 liquid scintillator detectors were kept",
                "at a distance of 1.5 m from the target at 0, 30,",
                "60 and 90 deg with respect to the beam direction.",
                "For 120 deg the detector was kept at a distance",
                "of 1.0 m."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "METHOD": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "TOF",
                "PSD"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " The neutron energy was determined by the",
                "TOF technique. The radio frequency signal from the",
                "beam buncher was used as the stop signal for the",
                "TOF. Standard pulse-shape discrimination technique",
                "using BC501 liquid scintillator was utilized to",
                "distinguish neutrons from photons."
              ]
            }
          ],
